[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: episode enrollment with journey-template instantiation, cross-institution data integration, journey-state maintenance, gap detection with severity-based routing, channel entry, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-context loading with caregiver awareness, conversation handling with state-grounded responses, output safety screening with scope verification, and care-team reporting with episode lifecycle management. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (cross-institution-integration governance, journey-template-as-code with care-management-leadership ownership, gap-detection-with-severity-based-routing, multi-institution-communication with consent and audit, and caregiver-aware conversation handling).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────── EPISODE ENROLLMENT + JOURNEY-TEMPLATE INSTANTIATION ──────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolled into a care episode]                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Triggered by clinical event (new diagnosis, scheduled       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      surgery, discharge from high-risk admission, transplant     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      evaluation, complex pediatric encounter, others)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-management or navigation team identifies the episode   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Journey template selected per episode type                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Template instantiated with patient-specific values:         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care team of record, scheduled events, expected timeline,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      documented diagnoses, medication list, language and         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      channel preferences, designated caregivers, consent         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      scopes, escalation contacts                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient reviews and consents                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver consent captured where applicable                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: signed enrollment record; instantiated journey;       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    longitudinal-store initialization]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────── CROSS-INSTITUTION DATA INTEGRATION ───────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Inbound data sources]                                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Primary EHR (FHIR API, HL7 v2 streams)                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - External-institution FHIR APIs (where Cures Act-enabled    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and data-sharing-agreement-permitted)                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - HIE queries (regional/state HIE document retrieval)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Direct messaging (inbound C-CDAs, structured documents)    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Carequality / CommonWell / TEFCA queries                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Payer APIs (eligibility, prior auth status, claims)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pharmacy APIs (prescription fill data)                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Lab-network APIs (results)                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Imaging-network integrations (PACS bridge, results)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient-uploaded documents (with OCR + entity extraction)  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient-reported information (via conversation)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Normalization layer]                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-source FHIR-style normalization                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Source attribution preserved                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Freshness timestamp per record                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Duplicate detection across sources                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conflict surfacing (different sources disagree)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Storage architecture]                                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Working store: per-patient normalized FHIR-style records   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Source archive: original raw payloads with provenance      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Event stream: data-arrival events for journey-state update │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: normalized cross-institution patient view with       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    source attribution and freshness tracking]                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────── JOURNEY-STATE MAINTENANCE ────────────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Journey state model]                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active episode: type, phase, milestones                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scheduled events: appointments, procedures, scans, labs    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - In-flight workflows: referrals, prior authorizations,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      eligibility checks, pre-procedure clearances               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Completed events: with results / outcomes                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care team of record: providers, navigators,                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      case managers, designated caregivers                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open items: pending actions by patient,                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pending actions by care team, pending external             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      institution actions                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open questions: items the patient has surfaced or          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the assistant has flagged                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [State update triggers]                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Inbound data event from any source                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversation-derived patient-reported update               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team-side update via care-team interface              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-based progression (appointment now in past)           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: current journey state with provenance for every      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    field]                                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────── GAP DETECTION WITH SEVERITY-BASED ROUTING ────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Gap detection rules per journey template]                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stalled prior authorization (over N days in flight)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Overdue follow-up (scheduled task past expected date)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Missed appointment without reschedule                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Missing pre-procedure clearance for upcoming procedure     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Medication-reconciliation conflict (duplicate, missing     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      taper, interaction)                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Dropped referral (sent but no receipt confirmation)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Results back but not communicated to patient               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scheduled-test conflict (two tests scheduled too close)    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team-of-record gap (referred specialist not yet       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      assigned)                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Journey-timeline-at-risk (next milestone slipping)         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Severity classification]                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Informational: surface to patient on next interaction      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Standard: notify patient via preferred channel             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team: alert assigned care manager / navigator         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Critical: immediate care-team alert, real-time channel     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Routing]                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per severity, per journey-template-specified contact       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - With escalation timer for unacknowledged alerts            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: gap events with severity and routing target]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
