[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-institution data integration with normalization and source attribution.** The integration layer is the most operationally complex part of the architecture. Per-source connectors, per-source normalization, source attribution preserved through the data flow, freshness timestamps, conflict surfacing, and graceful handling of partial data. The integration is the thing that makes the assistant possible; skipping it produces an assistant that can answer questions only about one institution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Journey-template-as-code with care-management-leadership ownership.** Each common care episode has a structured journey template, owned by the appropriate care-management leadership, version-controlled, and reviewed annually. Each instantiated journey is signed off by the patient's care-management team. The journey template specifies the milestones, the gap-detection rules, the escalation criteria, the engagement cadence, the role-of-record assignments, and the off-boarding criteria.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Gap detection with severity-based routing as architectural primitive.** The gap-detection pipeline runs continuously. Each gap category has a defined severity, a defined routing target, and a defined escalation timer if unacknowledged. The pipeline is part of production scope, not a phase-2 enhancement.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-institution communication with consent and audit.** With patient consent (granular, revocable, auditable), the assistant can communicate with institutions outside the deploying institution. The communication channel is appropriate to the recipient (FHIR-based messaging where supported, Direct messaging for clinical messages, fax-replacement APIs where used, fallback to phone-based human handoff). All cross-institution communication is audited with a coordination-decision-record entry.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Caregiver-aware conversation handling.** The assistant supports caregiver participation with documented consent, role-aware conversation handling, scope-appropriate responses, and audit. Identity-and-authorization-aware tool calls enforce the role boundary at the tool layer, not just at the prompt layer.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Provenance discipline as architectural floor.** Every factual statement the assistant makes traces to a source: which institution's record, which date, which document type. When the patient asks "how do you know that?" the assistant can answer. When the state is genuinely unknown, the assistant says so rather than producing a plausible-sounding guess.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous emergency screening across every utterance.** Same as the previous chapter 11 recipes. The assistant routes acute emergencies and crisis disclosures appropriately and does not try to handle them in-conversation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, gap-detection accuracy, escalation rate, episode-completion rate, patient-experience scores, and (where measurable) outcome metrics vary by language, channel, episode type, age cohort, sex, and social-determinant flags. Per-cohort dashboards are reviewed by clinical leadership, care-management operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When a primary integration source is unreachable (the institution's primary EHR, an external institution's FHIR API, the HIE, the Direct mailbox, the payer API), the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble pulling that data right now; for anything urgent please contact your care team at [number]." The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
